OL,3,CCompany fined after man run over by
OL,4,Ctruck on first day of work
OL,6,FAn investigation by the Health and
OL,7,FSafety Executive (HSE) found that he
OL,8,Fhad been hand picking waste after the
OL,9,Fconveyor belt they used had been
OL,10,Fremoved from use after it was
OL,11,Fsignificantly damaged in a fire a few
OL,12,Fmonths earlier.
OL,14,FEmployees were therefore required to
OL,15,Fwork directly on the ground, near
OL,16,Fmoving vehicles with no separation
OL,17,Fbetween them, putting the workers in
OL,18,Fconsiderable danger.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
