OL,3,CCompany fined after man run over by
OL,4,Ctruck on first day of work
OL,6,FThere was no risk assessment and a
OL,7,Flack of supervision for picking and
OL,8,Fsorting waste on the ground.
OL,10,FWheeldon Brothers Waste Limited, of
OL,11,FBury New Road, Bury, Lancashire,
OL,12,Fpleaded guilty to breaching Section
OL,13,F2(1) of the Health and Safety at Work
OL,14,Fetc Act 1974, was fined #250,000 and
OL,15,Fordered to pay #4102.32 costs at a
OL,16,Fhearing at Manchester Magistrates'
OL,17,FCourt on April 2.
OL,19,FAfter the hearing, HSE principal
OL,20,Finspector Lisa Bailey said: "This man
OL,21,Fis lucky to be alive.
